JOHANNESBURG President Jacob Zuma appointed members of the Board of the National Youth Development Agency (NYDA) on Friday.Zuma appointed John Mtsweni, Gloria Hlongwa, Joy Maimela, Thokozani Mokako, Kenneth Morolong, Yershen Pillay and Zandile Majozi.They will hold these positions for three years.READ: Youth can accelerate economic growth in SA - NYDAMtsweni will be the chairperson and deputised by Hlongwa. The President has wished the new members all of the best in their execution of the critical responsibility of leading youth development in South Africa, the Presidency said in a statement.NYDA has been dogged by controversy and there has been calls for the agency to be disbanded.eNCA